F\u233?yo warsagh \u225?r \u225?ligh nufngoi kangotau k\u233?t\u225?n Jerusalem. A njam f\u225? nufary\u233?ng k\u233?t\u233? Joden wanjen, Judam\u233?n \u225?r enmorm\u233?n y\u233?nan Gilgal m\u233?n\u225?t s\u225?i t\u233?fangongay\u233?nd a tautanaw\u233?t wanjem\u233?. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 16\~}
F\u233?yo Simei Gerane ambum, Benjaminenem\u233?n efe t\u233?morw\u233?n k\u233?t\u225?mam\u233?n Baurim ndarndar kufrotau a enmorm\u233?n y\u233?maf\u233? Judam\u233?n \u225?rf\u233? m\u233?n\u225?t s\u225?i t\u233?fangongay\u233?nd warsagh \u225?r Deifid. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 17\~}
A \u225?mb tausen \u225?r k\u233?tam\u233? Benjaminene \u225?r s\u233?nkota tamorw\u233?n y\u233?maf\u233?, tafnang\u233?r Siba, s\u233?nko \u225?r Solene m\u233?ngo \u225?s\u225?fogh \u225?r, a Sibane 15 ghak\u233?r ambum a 20 \u225?s\u225?fogh t\u233?fn\u225?r. F\u225? w\u233?keye kuwanotaw\u233?t k\u233?t\u225?n Joden m\u233?n\u225?t warsagh \u225?roe wanf\u233?gh\u233?t. {\cs57\b0\i0\ul0\scaps0\super\cf2\fs22 18\~}
